title: subst ICE when building specialization graph with `generic_const_exprs`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
I'm pretty sure this is a minimization of the ICE in #105573, cc @peter-kehl.

[playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=08c0c07f5faed4eec109eeae8a3113bd):

```rust
#![feature(generic_const_exprs)]

const DEFAULT: u32 = 1;

struct V<const U: usize = DEFAULT>
where
    [(); U]:;

trait Tr {}

impl Tr for V {}
```

<details>
